inlineContent.text: A video editor manages user interactions and provides the filesystem path of the edited movie to your delegate object (see
class are available only on devices that support video recording. Use a video editor when your intent is to provide an interface for movie editing. While the
class also lets a user trim movies, its primary roles are choosing saved pictures and movies, and capturing new pictures and movies.

class supports portrait mode only. This class is intended to be used as-is and doesn’t support subclassing. The view hierarchy for this class is private; don’t modify the view hierarchy. This class doesn’t support modifications to its appearance by use of overlay views.
